HERE ARE THE STEPS TO FULLY INSTALL AND RUN THE WEBSITE

1. Make a new folder

2. Navigate to the new folder with cd /FolderName
We will need 2 different folders inside our project folder, one being Frontend and one being Backend. First, we will create the Frontend

3. In the terminal navigated to your project folder, run the following code,
npm create vite@latest Frontend -- --template react

4. Go to the Frontend and install dependencies
cd Frontend
npm install

5. Find the App.jsx file that was created by running the code above, and replace it with the code in this git
Now we can set up the Backend

6. Create a backend folder in the project folder, and create a file named server.js inside the new folder. Copy and Paste the code from this git into that file

6. Open a terminal navigated to Backend, and run the following code
npm init -y
npm install express cors ws

NOW WE CAN ACTUALLY RUN THE WEBSITE
Steps to run
1. Upload the Arduino Code to the ESP32C3
2. Open a terminal navigated to Backend and run node server.js
3. Open a terminal navigated to Frontend and run npm run dev

MAKE SURE TO
- Under the line const char* backendURL = "http://172.20.10.5:3000/data" in your arduino code, replace the 172.20.10.5 part with your own ip (get by running ipconfig in terminal)
- Make sure your credentials are correct for your Wifi
